Name: trichostrongylosis
Definition: A trichostrongyloidiasis that involves infection of the small intestine with Trichostrongylus colubriformis or Trichostrongylus axei

Name: obsolete catatonic type schizophrenia subchronic state
Definition: A trichostrongyloidiasis that involves infection of the small intestine with Trichostrongylus colubriformis or Trichostrongylus axei

Name: obsolete catatonic type schizophrenia subchronic state with acute exacerbation
Definition: A trichostrongyloidiasis that involves infection of the small intestine with Trichostrongylus colubriformis or Trichostrongylus axei

Name: obsolete catatonic type schizophrenia chronic state with acute exacerbation
Definition: A trichostrongyloidiasis that involves infection of the small intestine with Trichostrongylus colubriformis or Trichostrongylus axei

Name: haemonchiasis
Definition: A trichostrongyloidiasis that involves parasitic infection of the ruminant abomasum by nematodes of the genus Haemonchus resulting in anemia

Name: ostertagiasis
Definition: A trichostrongyloidiasis that involves parasitic infection of the ruminant gastrointestinal tract by nematodes of the genus Ostertagia.
